COVID-19 Status 💉 🦠

As of 6:18PM PT today, over 1.6 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 27.8 thousand have died.

In the last day, 3.4 thousand new infections were reported and 52 deaths. Currently 2,502 are in the hospital and 779 are in the ICU. This is trending downwards.

Fortunately, 56 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 12 years and older, 12.5% have their 1st shot and 19.3% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is speeding up, but there are 7.9 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~77 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around Nov-18 when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children aged 11 or younger.

  • 73 in 100 have at least one vaccine dose,
    63 in 100 are fully vaccinated. From storage
    19 in 100 more could receive a dose.
